==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reassure
<hw>Re`as*sure"</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧`⟦adot⟧*sh⟦udd⟧r")</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To assure anew; to restore confidence to; to
free from fear or terror.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They rose with fear, . . . ⟦br⟧
Till dauntless Pallas <qex>reassured</qex> the rest.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To reinsure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reassurer</ent>⟦br⟧
